	<text>
		<body>
			<div type="entry">
				<pb facs="https://leaf.bucknell.edu/sites/default/files/2026-01/diary53.jpg"/>
				<dateline><date>Monday. 31.</date></dateline>
				<p><time>The morning</time> was <name key="Negetive" type="Weather">raw and
						chilly</name> - such as we have in September. <name type="Weather">Then the
						sun came out</name> about <time>ten o'clock</time> and was <name
						type="Weather">very hot</name>
					<time>until evening</time>, when it became <name type="weather">chilly</name>.
					Whisky has been ordered to be served to the men, an <objectName key="Drink"
						>ounce</objectName> in the morning I had determined to make application for
					a commission in <orgName role="Army">the regular army</orgName>, &amp; got a
					recommendation from <persName key="Thomas Bell" role="Soldier"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper072"
						>Lt. Col. Bell.</persName> I went over to <persName key="Jesse Reno"
						role="Soldier" cert="high"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper086"
						type="real">Gen Reno</persName>. He and <persName key="Ambrose Burnside"
						role="Soldier"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper008"
						>Gen Burnside</persName> both advised me to hold on to my rank here, as
						<orgName key="Military">the army</orgName> would be reorganized, and
					Captains would receive commissions to recruit companies: that I could not get a
					higher rank than 2nd Lieut &amp; would have to rise from it. <persName
						key="John Morris" cert="high"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper057"
						type="real">Morris </persName>&amp; I rode out about a half mile, where
						<persName key="Thomas Williams" role="Soldier"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper079"
						>Capt. Williamson</persName> was building a <objectName key="Building"
						>fort</objectName>. This is large to contain 8 acres, an <objectName
						key="Building">enclosed fort</objectName>, &amp; is about a half mile from
						<placeName role="River" key="Trent River"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_gazetteer.xml#linnpl083"
						>the Trent</placeName>. Another is to be built 3/4 of a mile further toward
						<placeName role="River" cert="unknown" key="Neuse River"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_gazetteer.xml#linnpl058"
						>the Neuse<precision match="@ref" precision="high"/></placeName>, &amp;
					about a half mile from it. We had dress parade <time>this evening</time> &amp;
						<persName key="George Shorkley" role="Soldier"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper002"
						>Lt. Shorkley</persName> acted as adjutant, <persName key="Daniel Bible"
